      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>With some 700 ethnic studies programs at United States universities, I have to wonder why Robin Shulman (letter, April 19) chose to attend Columbia College, "which has none." The idea that a university should bend its curriculum to student demands is outrageous.</p>
        <p>If Columbia wants to require six semesters of Western civilization at the (understandable) exclusion of other subject matter, that is the prerogative of that institution. Should the Juilliard School create an architecture program because flutists lock themselves in and demand one?</p>
        <p>MICHAEL MIKESELL New York, April 19, 1996</p>
      </block>
